    {"instruction": "Why does Elves play Natural Order?", "input": "", "output": "Natural Order sacrifices a green creature to tutor any green creature directly into play. In Elves, this means sacrificing a 1-mana elf to get Craterhoof Behemoth, which gives all your creatures +X/+X and trample where X is your creature count. With 5+ elves in play, this is typically a one-shot kill. Natural Order also finds silver bullets like Endurance or Collector Ouphe from the toolbox."},
